From: ETK GTK Edition <mercurious>
Subject: [PATCH v0.7.4] anti-lock stage 4 (ffs-v5, flip-status force-retire)
 + avwiden-v1 (access-violation readahead invalidation)

Two nets in one build, both operator-cleared 2026-07-12.

FFS-V5 — flip-status force-retire (anti-lock stage 4). The remaining ~50%
RECOVERY share on 00E59005 (N>=6 in one weekend): a keepalive rescue drops
the submit whose completion would have flipped; flip_status stays WAITING
forever and the guest parks in its cellGcmGetFlipStatus poll (GT5P EMAIN
0xbc92d0, ps3probe flip lens). The retire runs on the rsx thread inside the
stage-2 watchdog cadence and replays handle_emu_flip's completion tail
(flip_status -> DONE + flip-handler interrupt). Gated on a rescue having
occurred inside the WAITING window (forced-fence delta / stage-2 arming /
FIFO-desync streak) so organic long waits are never touched. Default ON;
GTK_FLIP_RETIRE=0 kill-switch; GTK_FLIP_RETIRE_S threshold (3 s default);
GTK_FLIP_RETIRE_ANY=1 drops the rescue gate (diagnostic).

AVWIDEN-V1 — access-violation readahead. GT HD at LOCKED-60 burns
13.3/20.5/14.8% of ALL cycles (three bog samples) in on_access_violation:
one PPU thread streaming writes through protected pages, one fault per 4K
page, every frame. On a WRITE fault the handler now additionally
invalidates a readahead span AHEAD of the faulting page (default 65536 =
16 pages) so a linear writer takes one fault per span. The faulting page
keeps the stock single-address call (exact violation_handled semantics —
a neighbor-only hit must never claim the fault page as handled); the
readahead result is deliberately dropped, which is safe by construction:
deferred-cause flushables are returned untouched (they heal via their own
later fault) and dirtied non-flushables refault at most once. Read faults
stay precise. Default ON; GTK_AV_READAHEAD=0 kill-switch or byte count
(4K..16M, page-rounded).

Instrumentation: perfstat line gains av= (fault delta per interval) and
fr= (cumulative flip retires); new forced-fence accessor
vk::etk_fence_forced_count().

Self-IDs "GTK Edition v0.7.4".
Base: v0.0.41-19544-60c9705a + 0.7.0 set + perfstat-v1 + semapark-v2.
Design: ETK dossiers KersConcept_20260712.md (access-violation = the
GT HD KPI lever) + SessionHandoff_20260710_DynoAttribution.md (ffs-v5).

